Cape Town – Brackenfell police are seeking the assistance of the public in locating the whereabouts of Charne Kruger, who has been missing since Sunday. The 29-year-old Kruger, from Brackenfell, was last seen by her mother at about 10.30am on Sunday at their residence, Western Cape police spokesperson Siyabulela Malo said on Wednesday. "Kruger is about 1.6 metres tall, weighs about 56kg, has long brown hair and blue eyes. She also have a tattoo at the back of her neck," Malo said. "It is unknown what she was wearing during the time of her disappearance." Police urge anyone with information that can assist in locating the whereabouts of Kruger to contact the investigating officer, Warrant Officer Raymond Saville, of the Brackenfell police on 021 980 5737 or alternatively Crime Stop on 08600 10111. The Kraaifontein police are also trying to find the 23-year-old Mary Mangwanya, who went missing on November 18. She was last seen in Wallacedene at 2pm and said she was going to a shop. She is mentally challenged and has not returned since. Mangwanyawas wearing a black flowered dress and black high heels. If you have information, contact the Kraaifontein detectives at 079 893 9857 or 021 980 6533 or the Pink Ladies at 072 214 7439 or 083 378 4882 or alternatively 08600 10111.    